'generate_query[1].predict' predictor demos: [Example({'augmented': True, 'context': ['Gymnocladus | Gymnocladus (Neo-Latin, from Greek γυμνὀς, "gymnos", naked + κλάδος, "klados", branch) is a small genus of leguminous trees. The common name coffeetree is used for this genus.', 'Gymnocladus chinensis | Gymnocladus chinensis, the soap tree or Chinese coffeetree, is a tree in the subfamily Caesalpinioideae of the pea family Fabaceae, native to central China. It grows slowly and is apparently extremely rare. The leaves have huge bipinnate leaves starting purple then shading to green.', 'Nautilocalyx | Nautilocalyx is a genus of plant in family Gesneriaceae.'], 'question': 'Which is a genus of tree, Gymnocladus or Nautilocalyx?', 'reasoning': 'The question asks whether Gymnocladus or Nautilocalyx is a genus of a tree. From the context, Gymnocladus is a genus of leguminous trees, while Nautilocalyx is a genus of plants in the family Gesneriaceae. Therefore, Gymnocladus is the genus of a tree.', 'search_query': 'Which genus is Gymnocladus or Nautilocalyx a part of?'}) (input_keys=None), Example({'augmented': True, 'context': ['Scottish Deerhound | The Scottish Deerhound, or simply the Deerhound, is a large breed of hound (a sighthound), once bred to hunt the Red Deer by coursing.', 'Dogo Argentino | The Dogo Argentino, also known as the Argentine Mastiff, is a large, white, muscular dog that was developed in Argentina primarily for the purpose of big-game hunting, including wild boar; the breeder, Antonio Nores Martínez, also wanted a dog that would exhibit steadfast bravery and willingly protect its human companion. It was first bred in 1928, from the Cordoba Fighting Dog along with a wide array of other breeds including the Great Dane.', 'Scottish tenor drum | The Scottish tenor drum is a musical instrument used within Scottish pipe bands. It is a double-headed membranophone that is held vertically with one head up, one head down, and played with soft mallets on the top head only. Common sizes of drums are 15, 16, 18, or 20 inch in diameter, with 12, 14, or 16 inch depth. The playing style of the Scottish tenor drum has varied throughout the years, but there is typically a variation of the combination of swings (or flourishes) and rhythmic accompaniment to the Scottish snare drum and the Great Highland Bagpipes. It is similar to the more common marching band style tenor drum.'], 'question': 'Are the Dogo Argentino and the Scottish Deerhound large or small dogs?', 'reasoning': 'The Dogo Argentino is described as a large, white, muscular breed developed for big-game hunting, and the Scottish Deerhound is noted as a large breed bred for hunting red deer. Both are explicitly large dogs based on the provided context.', 'search_query': 'No additional search is required as the information is directly available in the context.'}) (input_keys=None), Example({'augmented': True, 'context': ['American Dream Meadowlands | American Dream Meadowlands (ADM) is a retail and entertainment complex under construction in the Meadowlands Sports Complex in East Rutherford, New Jersey that will contain over 500 stores. It was first proposed in 2003 by the Mills Corporation as the "Meadowlands Xanadu". After the bankruptcy of that company in 2007, the project was taken over by Colony Capital. In May 2009, construction stalled due to the bankruptcy of Lehman Brothers. The Triple Five Group announced intent to take over the mall in May 2011, and on July 31, 2013, officially gained control of the mall and the surrounding site.', 'Meadowlands Hospital Medical Center | The Meadowlands Hospital Medical Center (MHMC), a for-profit hospital, is located at 55 Meadowlands Parkway in Secaucus, New Jersey. Established in 1976 as a non-profit, it was purchased in December 2010 while near bankruptcy by MHA LLC, owned and operated by Richard Lipsky (a former anesthesiologist), Tamara Dunaev, Pavel Pogodin, and Anastasia Burlyuk.', 'The Meadowlands (album) | The Meadowlands is the third studio album by American indie rock band The Wrens. It was released by Absolutely Kosher Records on September 9, 2003 and in the UK and Europe two years later on September 19, 2005 by LO-MAX Records. A UK limited edition version with two extra tracks, "Such a Pretty Lie" and "Nervous and Not Me", was released on February 27, 2006. The album was named after the New Jersey Meadowlands, the wetlands near the Wrens\' home in New Jersey.'], 'question': 'In what year did the company file for bankruptcy that had Bergen Ballpark as part of its Meadowlands Sports Complex?', 'reasoning': 'The question asks for the year a company filed for bankruptcy that included Bergen Ballpark as part of its Meadowlands Sports Complex. The context mentions that the Meadowlands Sports Complex, proposed by Mills Corporation in 2003, had construction halted in 2007 due to the bankruptcy of Mills Corporation. Therefore, the bankruptcy year is 2007.', 'search_query': 'The search query to find the bankruptcy year of the company associated with the Meadowlands Sports Complex is: "When did Mills Corporation file for bankruptcy?"'}) (input_keys=None)]

'generate_answer.predict' predictor demos: [Example({'augmented': True, 'context': ['Gymnocladus | Gymnocladus (Neo-Latin, from Greek γυμνὀς, "gymnos", naked + κλάδος, "klados", branch) is a small genus of leguminous trees. The common name coffeetree is used for this genus.', 'Gymnocladus chinensis | Gymnocladus chinensis, the soap tree or Chinese coffeetree, is a tree in the subfamily Caesalpinioideae of the pea family Fabaceae, native to central China. It grows slowly and is apparently extremely rare. The leaves have huge bipinnate leaves starting purple then shading to green.', 'Nautilocalyx | Nautilocalyx is a genus of plant in family Gesneriaceae.', 'Gymnocalycium | Gymnocalycium, commonly called chin cactus, is a genus of about 70 South American species of cactus. The genus name "Gymnocalycium" (from Greek, "naked calyx") refers to the flower buds bearing no hair or spines.', 'Gymnodinium | Gymnodinium is a genus of dinoflagellates. It is one of the few naked dinoflagellates, or species lacking armor (cellulosic plates). Since 2000, the species which had been considered to be part of "Gymnodinium" have been divided into several genera, based on the nature of the apical groove and partial LSU rDNA sequence data. Amphidinium was redefined later.'], 'question': 'Which is a genus of tree, Gymnocladus or Nautilocalyx?', 'reasoning': 'The context specifies that Gymnocladus is a genus of leguminous trees, while Nautilocalyx is a genus of plants in the family Gesneriaceae, specifically cacti. Therefore, Gymnocladus is the genus of the tree.', 'answer': 'Gymnocladus'}) (input_keys=None), Example({'augmented': True, 'context': ['Scottish Deerhound | The Scottish Deerhound, or simply the Deerhound, is a large breed of hound (a sighthound), once bred to hunt the Red Deer by coursing.', 'Dogo Argentino | The Dogo Argentino, also known as the Argentine Mastiff, is a large, white, muscular dog that was developed in Argentina primarily for the purpose of big-game hunting, including wild boar; the breeder, Antonio Nores Martínez, also wanted a dog that would exhibit steadfast bravery and willingly protect its human companion. It was first bred in 1928, from the Cordoba Fighting Dog along with a wide array of other breeds including the Great Dane.', 'Scottish tenor drum | The Scottish tenor drum is a musical instrument used within Scottish pipe bands. It is a double-headed membranophone that is held vertically with one head up, one head down, and played with soft mallets on the top head only. Common sizes of drums are 15, 16, 18, or 20 inch in diameter, with 12, 14, or 16 inch depth. The playing style of the Scottish tenor drum has varied throughout the years, but there is typically a variation of the combination of swings (or flourishes) and rhythmic accompaniment to the Scottish snare drum and the Great Highland Bagpipes. It is similar to the more common marching band style tenor drum.', "Information seeking behavior | Information seeking behavior refers to the way people search for and utilize information. The term was coined by Thomas D. Wilson in his 1981 paper, on the grounds that the then current 'information needs' was unhelpful as a basis for a research agenda, since 'need' could not be directly observed, while how people behaved in seeking information could be observed and investigated. However, there is increasing work in the information searching field that is relating behaviors to underlying needs.", 'Contextual searching | Contextual search is a form of optimizing web-based search results based on context provided by the user and the computer being used to enter the query. Contextual search services differ from current search engines based on traditional information retrieval that return lists of documents based on their relevance to the query. Rather, contextual search attempts to increase the precision of results based on how valuable they are to individual users.', 'Findability | Findability is a term for the ease with which information contained on a website can be found, both from outside the website (using search engines and the like) and by users already on the website. Although findability has relevance outside the World Wide Web, the term is usually used in that context. Most relevant websites do not come up in the top results because designers and engineers do not cater to the way ranking algorithms work currently. Its importance can be determined from the first law of e-commerce, which states "If the user can’t find the product, the user can’t buy the product." As of December 2014, out of 10.3 billion monthly Google searches by Internet users in the United States, an estimated 78% are made to research products and services online.'], 'question': 'Are the Dogo Argentino and the Scottish Deerhound large or small dogs?', 'reasoning': 'The Dogo Argentino and the Scottish Deerhound are both described as large breeds. The Dogo Argentino is noted for its muscular build and use in big-game hunting, while the Scottish Deerhound is bred for hunting red deer, both indicating their size category.', 'answer': 'large'}) (input_keys=None), Example({'augmented': True, 'context': ['American Dream Meadowlands | American Dream Meadowlands (ADM) is a retail and entertainment complex under construction in the Meadowlands Sports Complex in East Rutherford, New Jersey that will contain over 500 stores. It was first proposed in 2003 by the Mills Corporation as the "Meadowlands Xanadu". After the bankruptcy of that company in 2007, the project was taken over by Colony Capital. In May 2009, construction stalled due to the bankruptcy of Lehman Brothers. The Triple Five Group announced intent to take over the mall in May 2011, and on July 31, 2013, officially gained control of the mall and the surrounding site.', 'Meadowlands Hospital Medical Center | The Meadowlands Hospital Medical Center (MHMC), a for-profit hospital, is located at 55 Meadowlands Parkway in Secaucus, New Jersey. Established in 1976 as a non-profit, it was purchased in December 2010 while near bankruptcy by MHA LLC, owned and operated by Richard Lipsky (a former anesthesiologist), Tamara Dunaev, Pavel Pogodin, and Anastasia Burlyuk.', 'The Meadowlands (album) | The Meadowlands is the third studio album by American indie rock band The Wrens. It was released by Absolutely Kosher Records on September 9, 2003 and in the UK and Europe two years later on September 19, 2005 by LO-MAX Records. A UK limited edition version with two extra tracks, "Such a Pretty Lie" and "Nervous and Not Me", was released on February 27, 2006. The album was named after the New Jersey Meadowlands, the wetlands near the Wrens\' home in New Jersey.', 'Manomet Mills | The Manomet Mills are a historic textile mill complex on the north side of New Bedford, Massachusetts. They are located between Riverside Avenue and the Acushnet River, north of Manoment Street and the Whitman Mills. The complex consists of three Classical Revival brick buildings, built between 1903 and 1907. The main building, Mill No. 1, is a 54-bay three story structure that was built in 1903. It is attached to Mill No. 2 (1907), of similar size, by a single story brick structure. The third building is the Mill No. 2 Department Room (1907), a two story brick building that was originally connected to the other two via overhead bridges, now removed. The mill complex was the main operating site of the Manoment Mill Company, which produced cotton yarn until about 1928. The buildings were sold in that year to the Delaware Rayon Company, which went bankrupt in 1954. Mill No. 2 was then used by the Acushnet Process Company for the manufacture of golf balls, while Mill No. 1 continued to be used for rayon production, a chemically intensive and environmentally hazardous process.'], 'question': 'In what year did the company file for bankruptcy that had Bergen Ballpark as part of its Meadowlands Sports Complex?', 'reasoning': 'The context provided mentions that Mills Corporation, which was responsible for the Meadowlands Sports Complex, filed for bankruptcy in 2007. Although the question specifically refers to Bergen Ballpark, the available information points to Mills Corporation as the company associated with the Meadowlands Sports Complex that filed for bankruptcy in 2007.', 'answer': '2007'}) (input_keys=None)]

